This is the README file for SHPHP - Syntax Highlighter in PHP [language converter].


SHPHP uses the same file format to define languages as GNU Source-Highlight [http://www.gnu.org/software/src-highlite/].
So any GNU Source-Highlight language definition files can be simply converted to SHPHP language definition file.

The sh2php.pl script is written in Perl and requires the Parse::RecDescent module.

To convert language run in command line:
    perl sh2php.pl /path/to/GNU_Source_Highlight/language.lng >> /path/to/SHPHP/sh_language.php
